# Rule Authoring Standards

## Frontmatter Requirements

- Include `description`, `globs`, and `alwaysApply`.
- Default to file-scoped rules (`alwaysApply: false`) unless global behavior is truly required.
- Keep glob patterns specific to avoid accidental broad activation.

## Writing Guidelines

- Keep one concern per rule file.
- Use short, actionable instructions.
- Prefer concrete examples over abstract guidance.
- Keep rule content concise and easy to scan.

## Maintenance

- Update rules when project workflow changes.
- Remove stale or conflicting instructions promptly.
- Do not duplicate the same instruction across multiple rules unless scopes differ intentionally.
